OL,3,CPost Office confirms 115 branches to
OL,4,Cclose, with 1,000 workers at risk
OL,6,FThe Post Office has announced that
OL,7,Fmore than 100 of its branches are
OL,8,Fclosing as part of a
OL,9,F"transformational" plan to fix its
OL,10,Ffinances.
OL,12,FThe group said it plans to offload 115
OL,13,Fdirectly owned branches within its
OL,14,F11,500 network, which could see them
OL,15,Ftransferred to retail partners or
OL,16,Fpostmasters, or potentially closed.
OL,17,FThey are the only remaining branches
OL,18,Fdirectly owned by the Post Office,
OL,19,Fdown from close to 400 in 2010.
